{"author":{"id":"30a9cdd9e5369167dc36be4d3e5f98e516aa30b7571a17013bc815eef45f09c3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1445427935,"nonce":"E4TmFh/1hBQ5BKANCLlKuIaTvQc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTg2MzY3OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149863679"},"message":"\u003e Sorry, 3 lectures today. Just a quick note.\n\nNo problem. I really appreciate the feedback.\n\n\u003e  Not sure what we are aiming here. Do we want to mirror all R, perl ... tarballs?\n\nYes\n\n\u003e Databases? SNPeff databases? \n\nNo. That one definitely needs to be brought to the wider scientific community. \n\nMy aim here is a small, incremental improvement over where we were yesterday with URLs that disappear. That's all I want to solve, is to have a single, community maintained resource for this. I'll foot the bill myself if it's going to be an issue, s3 is pretty cheap and this is low, low processing power.\n\nI'd like to solve the \"we need to move tarballs around\" problem now. I'll probably add another field to the file with \"download_from\" where external URLs can be specified. That really wasn't the problem I was trying to solve but both you and @natefoo raised it. If a `download_from` field is specified/non-empty, then the updater script will ignore those lines and not download from the `upstream_url` and just point there so `gsl.py` can follow that link. Updating shortly..","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1445430151,"nonce":"QuXQ8TnWRmmuB1Io95Ev332JPQM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTg3NjcxNw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149876717"},"message":"Okay. Implemented. `gsl.py` and the package cache now support an `alterate_url` column (col 6) that specifies a URL where things should be downloaded from. Otherwise they'll be downloaded from a server URL that'll be codified in gsl.py (i.e. wherever the community package cache is hosted)\n\nSee the first line of https://github.com/erasche/package-cache/blob/master/urls.tsv","files":null}]}